</mj-text><mj-image href="https://coloradosun.com/2023/07/06/crystal-mill-closes-visitor-trail-marble-colorado/" src="https://i0.wp.com/newspack-coloradosun.s3.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/coloradosun230706inked.jpg?w=1200" padding="0px 0px 0px 0px" />
<!-- Cutline -->
<mj-text padding="0px 0px 0px 0px"><p class="cutline">Bad behavior by visitors to the 131-year-old Crystal Mill near Marble has caused its owner to remove a trail that once led people to one of the most photographed sites in Colorado. <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2023/07/06/crystal-mill-closes-visitor-trail-marble-colorado/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_source=The+Colorado+Sun+Newsletters&utm_campaign=SUNRISER_*|DATE:Ymd|*&utm_medium=email">Read more about the closure here</a>. (Drew Litton, Special to The Colorado Sun)</p></mj-text><mj-text>

<p>🌞 Every single public rate hearing for the Colorado Option insurance plan was canceled. <strong>John Ingold</strong> <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2023/07/05/colorado-option-health-insurance-hearings-canceled/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_source=The+Colorado+Sun+Newsletters&utm_campaign=SUNRISER_*|DATE:Ymd|*&utm_medium=email">explains why</a>.</p>

<p>🌞 Suncor Energy likely will have its operating permits renewed, but <strong>Michael Booth</strong> reports that recent discharges of benzene and PFAS &#8220;forever chemicals&#8221; to Sand Creek, and on to the South Platte River, <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2023/07/07/benzene-pollution-suncor-state-warns-fines/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_source=The+Colorado+Sun+Newsletters&utm_campaign=SUNRISER_*|DATE:Ymd|*&utm_medium=email">are making state regulators think twice</a> about what those permits demand.</p>

<p>🌞 Water watchers in the San Luis Valley have been fiercely defensive of the liquid gold flowing beneath their communities. Now they&#8217;ve taken the vigilance to the surface, with six county governments and a bunch of towns they include, joining to make it as difficult as possible to export aquifer water to the Front Range. <strong>Shannon Mullane</strong> <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2023/07/03/colorado-san-luis-valley-water-plan/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_source=The+Colorado+Sun+Newsletters&utm_campaign=SUNRISER_*|DATE:Ymd|*&utm_medium=email">has the details</a>.</p>

<p>🌞 People who live close to urban-adjacent oil and gas operations are used to high conflict over drilling and plenty of attention when mistakes are made. It&#8217;s different out on the Eastern Plains, where extraction seems to have always been part of the rhythm of life, but it can take what feels like forever for them to be remedied. <strong>Mark Jaffe</strong> went out to Eads, where a fifth-generation rancher is <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2023/07/05/oil-spill-kills-cows-western-operating-colorado/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_source=The+Colorado+Sun+Newsletters&utm_campaign=SUNRISER_*|DATE:Ymd|*&utm_medium=email">at war with the company drawing oil from under his land</a>.</p>

<p>🌞 Even $14,000 signing bonuses aren&#8217;t enough to persuade Colorado nurses to go to work at the state&#8217;s two mental health hospitals. <strong>Jennifer Brown </strong>explains how <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2023/07/06/state-mental-hospitals-nursing-shortage-jail/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_source=The+Colorado+Sun+Newsletters&utm_campaign=SUNRISER_*|DATE:Ymd|*&utm_medium=email">a shocking staff shortage</a> has huge implications for people with mental illnesses who are accused of serious crimes.</p>

<p>🌞 Good news! For the first time since 2019 Colorado is completely drought-free. Though reservoirs are filling, and parched soils are finally quenched, <strong>Shannon Mullane</strong> reports that if the historical trends play out this year, <a target="_blank"  href="https://coloradosun.com/2023/07/07/colorado-drought-free-for-the-first-time-since-2019/?utm_source=newsletter&utm_source=The+Colorado+Sun+Newsletters&utm_campaign=SUNRISER_*|DATE:Ymd|*&utm_medium=email">the conditions are only temporary</a>.</p>

